        "args": {
            "cmd": "cd /home/aludy/scires/Cloud_Spec_Exp/external/worktrees/oci-metagpt/metagpt/youki-2756 && grep -r -n 'LinuxDeviceType' --include='*.rs' | head -20"
        }
    }
]
```
Now I understand the issue. The bug is in the emulator in `v2/devices/emulator.rs`. When a device rule has no `type` field (like `{"allow": false, "access": "rwm"}` in the buggy config), `rule.typ()` returns `None`, and `unwrap_or_default()` for `LinuxDeviceType` likely returns `A` (all). This incorrectly triggers the "special case" wildcard behavior, clearing all rules and setting deny-all. In runc, a device rule without an explicit type is not treated as the wildcard 'a' type.

